On Thu, 21 Feb 2008, dcm(-at-)c-sw.com wrote:

> Perhaps unrelated -- perhaps not -- years ago I drove a Beetle Convertible
> with a whopping 36 HP motor.  After about 1/2 hour or so at
> close-to-highway speeds, I would lose power.  If I pulled off the road and
> sat for about 1/2 hour, the car would start and I could continue another
> 1/2 hour.  While stopped, if I tried to start the car before it was
> "ready", it would sound flooded and/or out-of-gas.

I had a similar problem in an old 40 horse, and after many months of
pulling my hair out I finally found that it was a tiny crack on the
vacuum side of the fuel line, when the engine comp warmed up the crack
opened enough that the engine sucked air and stalled and would not
run,  cooled off and the crack closed up and repeated the process.
about a half hour depending on outside temps

Bob


